# WASM Support

This plugin is configured with WASM support. Place your `.wasm` files in this directory.

## Getting Started

### Option 1: Rust (via wasm-pack)

1. Install [Rust](https://www.rust-lang.org/tools/install) and [wasm-pack](https://rustwasm.github.io/wasm-pack/installer/)
2. Create a Rust project: `wasm-pack new my-wasm`
3. Build: `wasm-pack build --target web`
4. Copy the `.wasm` output to this directory

### Option 2: AssemblyScript

1. Install: `npm install assemblyscript`
2. Create `assembly/index.ts` with your code
3. Build: `npx asc assembly/index.ts --outFile src/wasm/module.wasm`

## Usage

```typescript
import wasmModule from './wasm/module.wasm';

const instance = await WebAssembly.instantiate(wasmModule);
const { add } = instance.exports as { add(a: number, b: number): number };
```
